<node BACKGROUND_COLOR="#ffff00" CREATED="1493973994549" ID="ID_1378217582" MODIFIED="1493973995701" TEXT="The analogy of classes and objects with data types and variables does not hold good for the memory allocation in this case. Defi ning a variable will require a compiler to provide memory. On the contrary, whenever a class defi nition appears, the memory for the member functions is provided by the compiler. The memory for data members is provided when an object is defi ned from that class."/>
